f(n) = \sum\limits_{i=1}^{n} \frac{-5}{6^i}
0\leq m\leq n
r\not= 1
\sum_{k = m}^{m}ar^{k} = \frac{a(r^m - r^{n+1})}{1-r}.
\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{-5}{6^k} = \frac{(-5)(\frac{1}{6}-(\frac{1}{6})^{n+1})}{1-\frac{1}{6}}
 = (-6)\left(\frac{1}{6}-\left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^{n+1}\right)
 = (-1)\left(1-\left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^{n}\right)
 = \frac{1}{6^{n}} - 1
 \sum_{k=1}^n\frac{-5}{6^k}=-5\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{1}{6^k}=-5\sum_{k=1}^n\left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^k. 
